    <title>Advanced Foundation Maths - 1</title>
    <url>/2022/09/20/Advanced%20Foundation%20Maths%20-%201/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<link rel="stylesheet" class="aplayer-secondary-style-marker" href="/assets/css/APlayer.min.css"><script src="/assets/js/APlayer.min.js" class="aplayer-secondary-script-marker"></script><script class="meting-secondary-script-marker" src="/assets/js/Meting.min.js"></script><h1 id="Advanced-Foundation-Maths-1"><a href="#Advanced-Foundation-Maths-1" class="headerlink" title="Advanced Foundation Maths - 1"></a>Advanced Foundation Maths - 1</h1><h3 id="Seminar1"><a href="#Seminar1" class="headerlink" title="Seminar1"></a>Seminar1</h3><h4 id="Target"><a href="#Target" class="headerlink" title="Target"></a>Target</h4><ul>
<li>Function&amp;Inverse functions</li>
<li>Inequality</li>
<li>Quadratic equation</li>
<li>Completing the square 配方</li>
<li>Exponential and Logarithmic</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="Function-The-relation-between-two-sets"><a href="#Function-The-relation-between-two-sets" class="headerlink" title="Function: The relation between two sets"></a>Function: The relation between two sets</h4><p>$f(x)=-\sqrt{x} \ \ \ \ D_f={1,4,6,16,25}$ function equals to minus square root of x </p>
<p>$f:A-&gt;B$   A is domain and B is co-domian </p>
<ul>
<li>对应关系<ul>
<li>one-&gt;one 有且仅有一个x对应一个y</li>
<li>many-&gt;one 存在两个及以上x对应一个y</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>co-domain<ul>
<li>range==co-domain: onto</li>
<li>range &lt; co-domain: into </li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h5 id="Composition-of-function"><a href="#Composition-of-function" class="headerlink" title="Composition of function"></a>Composition of function</h5><p>$(fog)(x)=f(g(x))$ </p>
<p>Read: f over g x equals to f of g(x)</p>
<p>$R_f ⊆ D_g$</p>
<h5 id="Inverse-function"><a href="#Inverse-function" class="headerlink" title="Inverse function"></a>Inverse function</h5><p>y is a subject to formula -&gt;  x is a subject to formula</p>
<h5 id="Modulus-function"><a href="#Modulus-function" class="headerlink" title="Modulus function"></a>Modulus function</h5><p>$f(x)= |x|$  function of x equals to modulus </p>
<h5 id="Exponential-function"><a href="#Exponential-function" class="headerlink" title="Exponential function"></a>Exponential function</h5><p>$y=f(x)=a^x$  a to the power of x</p>
<h5 id="Logarithmic-function"><a href="#Logarithmic-function" class="headerlink" title="Logarithmic function"></a>Logarithmic function</h5><p>$y=f(x)=log_ax$  x is logarithym of y to base a </p>
<h5 id="Translation"><a href="#Translation" class="headerlink" title="Translation"></a>Translation</h5><ul>
<li>Move:<ul>
<li>$f(x)\rightarrow f(x)+a$  f(x)  shifted upward/downward by a distance of a units</li>
<li>$f(x)\rightarrow f(x+a)$  f(x)  shifted to the right/left by a distance of a units </li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Stretch: $f(x) \rightarrow  kf(x) \ \ k&gt;1$ k·f(x) is stretching of the graph of f(x) vertically <code>/vɜːtɪkli/</code> by a factor of k</li>
<li>Compressions: $f(x) \rightarrow  kf(x) \ \ 0&lt;k&lt;1$ k·f(x) is compressioning of the graph of f(x) vertically by a factor of $1\over k$</li>
</ul>
<h5 id="Polynomial-function-多项式"><a href="#Polynomial-function-多项式" class="headerlink" title="Polynomial function 多项式"></a>Polynomial function 多项式</h5><ul>
<li><p>It can be expresseded as a sum of finitely many terms of the form $ax^n$</p>
</li>
<li><p>read: x raised to n or x to the pwer of n -&gt; $x^n$  </p>
</li>
<li><p>Degree = n</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
P(x)=a_0+a_1x+a_2x^2+...+a_nx^n \ \ n\in N^*</script><p>| Degree | Name      |<br>| ——— | ————- |<br>| 0      | Constant  |<br>| 1      | Linear    |<br>| 2      | Quadratic |<br>| 3      | Cubic     |<br>| 4      | Quartic   |<br>| 5      | Quintic   |</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="Example"><a href="#Example" class="headerlink" title="Example"></a>Example</h4><ol>
<li>Prove that $(\frac{x^p}{x^q})^{p^2+pq+q^2}·(\frac{x^q}{x^r})^{q^2+qr+r^2}·(\frac{x^r}{x^p})^{r^2+rp+p^2} = 1$<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
LHS=(x^{p-q})^{p^2+pq+q^2}·(x^{q-r})^{q^2+qr+r^2}·(x^{r-p})^{r^2+rp+p^2} \\ =x^{p^3-q^3}·x^{q^3-r^3}·x^{r^3-p^3} \\ =x^0 =1=RHS</script></li>
</ol>
<ol>
<li><script type="math/tex; mode=display">
{1\over{1+x^{a-b}+x^{a-c}}}+{1\over{1+x^{b-c}+x^{b-a}}}+{1\over{1+x^{c-a}+x^{c-b}}}\\
=\frac{x^{b+c}}{x^{b+c}+x^{a+c}+x^{a+b}}+\frac{x^{a+b}}{x^{a+b}+x^{b+c}+x^{a+c}}+\frac{x^{a+c}}{x^{a+c}+x^{b+a}+x^{b+c}}\\
=1</script></li>
</ol>
]]></content>
